I've created a comprehensive airline database schema with sample data. Here's what's included:

Core Tables:


Airports: Stores airport information including coordinates
Aircraft: Manages fleet information
Flights: Tracks all flight details
Fare Classes: Different ticket classes with their benefits
Seats: Aircraft seating configuration
Passengers: Customer information
Bookings: Reservation records


Key Features:


Data integrity with foreign key constraints
Check constraints to prevent invalid data
Useful views for common queries
Sample data to get started


Common Use Cases:


Flight scheduling and tracking
Seat availability checking
Booking management
Passenger information management
